00:01:36.630 --> 00:01:42.600
In 1951, Battersea Park was the host for a
fun fair as part of a Festival for Britain.

00:01:42.600 --> 00:01:43.450
May

00:01:43.450 --> 00:01:49.479
30th 1972, what should be a day for people
to enjoy, laugh and celebrate turned into

00:01:49.479 --> 00:01:49.740
a day

00:01:49.740 --> 00:01:55.250
of terror. The fun fair included an infamous
ride called "The Big Dipper" a three car

00:01:55.250 --> 00:02:01.350
wooden train which rode at 50 mph. The ride
was always the main spotlight and brought

00:02:01.350 --> 00:02:01.409
a

00:02:01.409 --> 00:02:07.420
long line up of people, mostly children. That
day 31 people had boarded the ride. The ride

00:02:07.420 --> 00:02:12.489
was going as planned until it reached 15 metres
above the park. Suddenly, the train

00:02:12.489 --> 00:02:17.510
detached from its drive chain earlier than
it should have, the operator in charge could

00:02:17.510 --> 00:02:17.590
be

00:02:17.590 --> 00:02:22.760
seen struggling to activate the breaks. The
train slipped backwards and hit a tight turn

00:02:22.760 --> 00:02:27.840
and derailed from its tracks. Two teenage
boys including an eight-year-old girl died

00:02:27.840 --> 00:02:28.270
at the

00:02:28.270 --> 00:02:33.580
scene...two other children died later. The
park amassed several charges including

00:02:33.580 --> 00:02:37.080
manslaughter, the ride was deemed as a "death
trap."

00:02:37.080 --> 00:02:37.980
