00:02:37.980 --> 00:02:42.970
The Mindbend is the world's largest indoor
roller coaster and it's situated in Edmonton

00:02:42.970 --> 00:02:50.400
mall in Alberta, Canada. Its first operation
date was on March 16th 1986 and everything

00:02:50.400 --> 00:02:55.530
went well, but exactly three months later
the unexpected occured. Upon completing the

00:02:55.530 --> 00:02:59.690
second inverted loop, missing bolts on the
left wheel assembly from one of

00:02:59.690 --> 00:03:03.390
the bogie caused the ride to disengage from
the track. This lead

00:03:03.390 --> 00:03:08.400
the train to stall at the top and sliding
backwards finally crashing into a concrete

00:03:08.400 --> 00:03:14.400
pillar. Three people died from the accident
and one was injured with his legs pointing

00:03:14.400 --> 00:03:15.819
opposite directions.

